本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:劉春美研究生(外文):Chun-mei Liu論文名稱:燕巢芭樂產業文化之形成與發展論文名稱(外文):The Formation and Development of Guava-Industrial Culture in Yenchao指導教授:陳坤宏指導教授(外文):Kung-Hung Chen學位類別:碩士校院名稱:國立臺南大學系所名稱:台灣文化研究所教學碩士班學門:人文學門學類:台灣語文學類畢業學年度:96語文別:中文論文頁數:148中文關鍵詞:人文景觀、地方感、產業文化、燕巢、芭樂外文關鍵詞:human landscape、sense of place、industrial culture、guava、Yenchao相關次數:

被引用:14點閱:745評分:下載:222書目收藏:0



本論文旨在研究燕巢芭樂產業文化之形成與發展，經由文獻、資料收集、田調訪問燕巢鄉實際從事芭樂產業之農民、產銷班班長、班員、芭樂苗圃園主、農會相關人員及自營中盤商及「農業區位」、「地方感」、「產業文化」等理論分析的方法，來研究1950年至2007年燕巢鄉農業及芭樂產業的變遷，藉以探討：一、芭樂的種植如何成為燕巢鄉的特色產業。二、燕巢鄉芭樂產業人文景觀的形成。三、燕巢芭樂產業文化的現況與問題。本研究發現：一、燕巢芭樂的品質確實獲得大家一致性的肯定。二、燕巢鄉地形、氣候、土壤、水資源等地理自然條件，加上燕巢鄉農業變遷之歷史文化、中山高速公路交通知開通、農業各項技術之改善及農會產銷制度的成功與燕巢鄉人口老化等各項人文因素，皆符合芭樂產業農業區位的形成與發展，芭樂產業乃得以成為燕巢鄉的特色產業。三、燕巢鄉芭樂產業文化的形成有「地方感的認同」、「鄉土教育的紮根」、「文史工作室的努力」和「社區營造的發展」等四大助力，也在這四個面向中呈現出燕巢芭樂產業文化的內涵。並印證由產業、生活、教育組成的產業文化結構與由政府機關、社區及民間團體等權力結構的協力關係，二者實可相輔相成，共榮燕巢芭樂產業文化。最後呼籲鄉公所、農會、學校、社區發展協會、援剿人文協會等團體，大家繼續深化燕巢芭樂產業文化，落實芭樂文化產業化，以為鄉民建立優質的生活文化。

This paper intends to study the formation and development of guava-industrial culture in Yenchao. By the methods of theoretical analysis including literature reference, data collection, visiting farmers who actually engaged in guava industry, consulting leaders and members of guava production and marketing department, nursery garden owners, relative personnel of agricultural association, sellers, and “location of agricultural”, “sense of place”, “industrial culture”, to perform the alternation of agriculture and guava industry in Yenchao during the period of 1950 to 2007, thus studying topics below. Firstly, how does the guava planting become the characteristic industry in Yenchao. Secondly, the formation of humanities landscape led by guava industrial culture in Yenchao.  Thirdly, the current status and problem about guava-industrial culture of Yenchao.   The results of the study represent hereby. Firstly, “Yenchao-guava” awards “brand-name” of its high quality. Secondly, the topography, climate, soil, water and other natural geographic conditions of Yenchao, accompanied with the factors such as historical and cultural changes of agriculture, rapid transport since high way facilitated, agricultural technology improvement, well-systematized production and marketing, and ageing population of this town, all are in compliance with the formation and development for guava industrial area of agriculture. Consequently, guava industry becomes the characteristic one in Yencho. Thirdly, there are four major power to form the guava-industrial culture of Yenchao. They are “indentity of hometown sense”, “built-up of local education”, “efforts of literature and history studio”, and “development of community-build”, which also perform the contents of guava-industrial culture for Yenchao. The study also proves that the cultural structure of industry, life, and education can be in coordination with the government, community and civic groups, which therefore stands to benefit most for guava-industrial culture from the cooperation.    By the end of this paper, I would like to appeal to Yenchao township office, agricultural association, schools, association of community development, and Yuanchiao Humanities Society for deepening guava industrial-culture, so that to build up a high quality life for the Yenchao citizen.

